definition: to choose/to pick/to settle upon/to decide upon a candidate/to be selected for some role
to hit (the mark)/to be hit by/to suffer/to win (a prize, a lottery)

sentences.english: The President's envoy to the conference has not yet been chosen.
sentences.chinese: 總統的外交使節參加會議尚未被選中。

sentences.english: Accept the default in which all columns of the table are selected.
sentences.chinese: 使用默認值，其中這個表的所有列都是選中的。

sentences.english: All artifacts in the selected repository or project will be listed.
sentences.chinese: 選中儲存庫或者項目中的所有工件都會列出來。

sentences.english: Double-click the first JLabel to select its display text.
sentences.chinese: 雙擊第一個JLabel以選中其顯示文本。

sentences.english: I considered you while doing my Horoscope last night, and meditated.
sentences.chinese: 昨晚我施法佔星術時選中了你。

sentences.english: Imes picked Rose from all the beautiful girls in the school to be a model.
sentences.chinese: 艾姆斯從全校那些美麗的女孩子中選中露絲做模特兒。

sentences.english: The novel I had thrown away was chosen by the Book Society.
sentences.chinese: 我一度扔掉的那部小說後來被書社選中了。

sentences.english: In this first step, the customer data is checked.
sentences.chinese: 在此第一步中，選中客戶數據。

sentences.english: Please select all the photos you request for the high-resolution version, and then click the bottom button.
sentences.chinese: 請在選中所有所需高像素圖片後，點擊下方按鈕。

sentences.english: IT chose the red sweater ratIT dawn the pink first.
sentences.chinese: 她選中那件紅毛衣而無所不能那件粉紅色的。

sentences.english: The system sends notices to the selected providers.
sentences.chinese: 系統向選中的提供者發送通知。

sentences.english: This maps it to the selected record type.
sentences.chinese: 這樣可以將它映射到選中的記錄類型中。

sentences.english: A maiden with many wooers ofter chooses the worst.
sentences.chinese: 有許多人向她求婚的少女，常常選中最差的一個。

sentences.english: If a quick catalog has previously been selected, that catalog will be loaded and displayed.
sentences.chinese: 如果先前有快速星表被選中，在目錄中就會有顯示。

sentences.english: Miko:If I had not selected it, I would not have been chosen to hunt you down.
sentences.chinese: 如果我沒有選過這項專長，就不會被選中來抓捕你們。

sentences.english: This is something we are working on with selected beta customers.
sentences.chinese: 這也正是我們和被選中的測試用戶一起在做的事情。

definition: to lock (a door)/to close with a latch/to lock into place/a lock/a latch/to lock a computer file (to prevent it being overwritten)/to lock (denying access to a computer system or device or files, e.g. by password-protection)/to focus attention on/to target

abbr. for 國民大會|国民大会, National Assembly of the Republic of China (extant during various periods between 1913 and 2005)/abbr. for 新加坡國立大學|新加坡国立大学, National University of Singapore (NUS)/abbr. for 印度國民大會黨|印度国民大会党, Indian National Congress (INC)/abbr. for 馬來西亞印度國民大會黨|马来西亚印度国民大会党, Malaysian Indian Congress (MIC)
to view as/to see as/to consider to be/to deem
auxiliary verb introducing future action: may (be able to)/will (cause)/should (enable)/going to
to leave a place where some event is taking place/(of an actor) to exit/(sports) to leave the field/(of an audience) to leave
